<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>What is an AI SEO agent?</strong></p>
<p>An AI SEO agent is an autonomous AI system that plans and executes multi-step SEO tasks without requiring a human prompt for each step. It uses real data access, tool integration, persistent memory, and independent decision-making to complete SEO workflows from research through publishing. This differs from AI tools that require manual prompting for each task.</p>
<p><strong>How is an AI SEO agent different from ChatGPT?</strong></p>
<p>ChatGPT is an AI tool. It responds to one prompt at a time. An AI SEO agent receives a goal (like "write and publish a blog post about local SEO") and autonomously handles every step: keyword research, competitor analysis, content writing, optimization, and publishing. ChatGPT needs a separate prompt for each of those tasks.</p>
<p><strong>Are AI SEO agents safe to use with Google?</strong></p>
<p>Yes, with caveats. Google evaluates content on quality, not production method. AI-generated content is not penalized if it meets quality standards. However, mass-producing low-quality content (which AI agents make easy) violates Google's spam policy on "scaled content abuse." Use quality gates and human review to stay safe.</p>
<p><strong>How much do AI SEO agents cost?</strong></p>
<p>Pricing ranges from $32/mo (KIVA, NightOwl) to $879/mo (WordLift enterprise). Most mid-range options cost $49-$149/mo. At $99/mo for 30 published articles, Stacc offers one of the lowest cost-per-article ratios at approximately $3.30 per article.</p>
<p><strong>Can AI SEO agents replace SEO agencies?</strong></p>
<p>For basic content creation and <a href="/glossary/technical-seo/">technical SEO</a> audits, yes. For strategic planning, competitive positioning, and custom campaigns, no. AI agents handle execution well. They do not replace the strategic thinking that experienced SEO professionals provide. The most effective approach combines AI agent execution with human strategy.</p>
<p><strong>Which AI SEO agent is best for small businesses?</strong></p>
<p>For small businesses that want hands-off SEO, a done-for-you agent like Stacc ($99/mo for 30 articles) is the most practical choice. For businesses that want more control, Frase ($49/mo) offers the broadest pipeline coverage. For budget-conscious businesses, NightOwl ($32/mo) provides basic agent functionality at the lowest price.</p>
<p>AI SEO agents are the most significant shift in SEO tooling since rank trackers went cloud-based. The technology is real, the cost savings are measurable, and the quality is improving every quarter. The businesses that adopt agents now build a compounding content advantage. The ones that wait will spend 3 times as much catching up later.</p>
